caption: The best pizza in the neighborhood and these garlic knots are out of this world. Love the meatballs too!
Best pizzeria in Brooklyn hidden gem. The best pizza comes out from the brick oven
Awesome!
Pizza was delicious. Very nice lady behind the counter. Highly recommended.

Uncle Frankie's is truly the BEST. And there are lots of great pizza spots in this neighborhood to compete with. Uncle Frankie's pizza is consistently so delicious and the ingredients always taste so fresh. It's always been delivered correctly and on time. Highly recommend getting the Bees Knees pizza and garlic knots (the calzones are also amazing!).

Its not easy to find a good vegan pizza,, but here it is! Delicious food and amazingly friendly, personable,  and genuine humans. Even if the food was bad (which it is FAR from) I'd constantly be visiting them!
Neighborhood staple
Always good slices and friendly staff. It's our neighborhood slice shop and we couldn't be happier.
Amazing garlic knots and super prompt delivery
The pesto pizza is like a salt bomb. Almost inedible. It came not sliced.  Had the bing sting before which was great.

I’m in NY for vacay and Uncle Frankie’s is the first place I stopped in for some grub. Danny behind the counter was welcoming and thoughtful. The meat lovers pizza was more than delicious and I ate well for $7. The restaurant was clean and had a great atmosphere. Run, don’t walk, to Uncle Frankie’s!
This spot is worth a visit. They serve large portions for fair rates. Constantly clean and with awesome character. I highly recommend this place.
Tasty neighborhood pizza
Love this place, great food, great people and even better service

Amazing food! Quality ingredients 👍🏼 My favorite is the chicken buffalo pizza! Friendly staff & very cute atmosphere. Everyone is polite and makes you feel at home. Love the magic tricks they do for the kids. This place goes above and beyond.  Love the make your own pizza nights for the kids!
Finally good pizza on the block!
It's been a while since I have been here. Definitely a downward spiral. Long wait for mediocre product. Won't be back.
Delicious brick oven pizza,  the owner Danny was very friendly and the establish was clean and inviting
A gem in the neighborhood. Friendly owner and great tasting pizza .
Pizza is very good. Garlic knots may be the best I've ever had
I have went into this place a couple minutes ago, and the cheese is so good! I would recommend this pizza place to anyone because it's really great to have for lunch.

Chicken Parm was chopped up meat with the breading separated from the chicken covered up with cheap melted mozzarella also I specified Al dente pasa and they gave me extremely over cooked pasta , same thing the meatballs they chopped them up extremely dry meat with mushy pasta , worse place ever !! Only went there cause I live in the neighborhood and what a mistake trying to Eat local
Good Brick Oven Pizza. Friendly service. Good sized seating area

This little place was awesome great tasting Pizza. Will definitely be back because I could taste the dish being enjoyed by another customer. Can't remember the name but remember where its located on the menu. TASTY
Try Garlic knots, delicious. I would eat a whole dozen of them.
Unbelievable pizza and calzone. My kids are everything with out interruption and enjoyed it. Definitely my new spot.
Best Pizza Evaaaaa !!!!!
So fresh and delicious! Love the new owner he was very kind and welcoming unlike the previous owner. Highly recommend coming here!!
Good pizza.  Dont need anything more....
Amazing pizza
Excellent pizza, bread, heros, salads and entrees. All made with care!

The food used to be good like 2 months ago 3 months ago. But recently the food taste horrible. I purchased the ex delicious fried Oreos, and it was very soggy and oily. The pizza is NOT cooked and it is very doughy. It was wet in my mouth and didn’t taste good AT ALL. I don’t know what happened maybe there is a new chef ? But the food taste completely different. The sauce taste like it has been changed. I used to love going there after work but now it’s just different. I am very disappointed, VERY!
I ordered  a grilled chicken  ceaser  salad.  It was good but at  $16.00 a total RIP off.
It was great
The owner is so awesome! He always greets my son and I with a magic trick and of course my little 1 loves it!

Came with my family and denny was so friendly with the kids, they entertained us with magic tricks and shafira checked on the tables to make sure everything was well. We ordered 4 pies. The pizza was so fresh and we also got the chicken cesar salad , every thing tasted amazing. We were greeted as soon as we walked in. We will definitely be back
Uncle Frankie himself is a personable guy

Went there for a kid's birthday party. The owners were very nice and very accommodating. Not sure what his name was, but he was active and patient with the group of kindergarteners! They were able to make their own pizza out of dough, sauce and cheese. He explained to the children how to knead the dough, how much sauce to put on and how to sprinkle the cheese on  Adults were given a sample of their apps and also some slices of their plain pizza. Everything was delicious. During the pizza making process, he did card tricks to keep the children in their seats and interested. Towards the end, he made balloon animals for all of them. Great service and great food. They were also able to serve other people while all this was going on. Very impressive!

This place is great! Especially for families. The food is delicious and the staff are great with kids. We have gone there several times and each time are treated to card tricks and fun banter.  We recently celebrated my daughter birthday there and had amazing food, card tricks, balloon animals, and an overall awesome time.  So glad this is in the neighborhood!

Was walking past and randomly walked in. Best decision I ever made! I'm vegan and unfortunately there were not any vegan slices available (I would have had to order an entire pie), but the garlic knots were made vegan without the cheese and they were DELICIOUS! Best garlic knots I've ever had! The dough was perfection and everyone working there was so sweet. Will definitely return!
Best garlic knots I’ve ever had. They make them to order, and they’re out of this world. The pizza here is fantastic as well. Uncle Frankie clearly knows dough!
Fried zucchini was unbelievable and pizza was cooked perfect. Staff was friendly and entertaining!!!!  Peanut butter cheesecake was to die for!
I came here one day with my oldest daughter and we both loved the pizza and the vibe
Best pizza ever!!
I took a pizza to go from here couple days ago and it was one of the best pizzas I ever had. Marinara sauce is done perfectly!
Absolutely delicious.

The food is billed as Sicilian specifically instead of Italian, which in my opinion is always a good sign. I wasn't disappointed. The lasagna was homestyle and comforting, with just the right mix of spices, basil, meat and cheese. I also had the chocolate mousse which I was pleasantly surprised to see had a bit of a cake-like pie crust- a really nice texture to buttress the mousse. Great staff and it's impossible to complain about the prices (they were 20% lower than I expected). This place is a no brainer for a cozy spot you can enjoy a conversation in while getting a lot of value for some amazing dishes. And they have the "real" Cokes! A must with a pizza
One of the best pizzas I’ve ever had.
Amazing man a true artist  chef. So happy to have him so close in our hood.

I dined here before it switched owners and names but ordered delivery prior to visiting in person. The interior decor is nice and comfortable, a bit of an elevated pizza place. The baby arugula salad and pancetta pizza was fantastic, however, the tomatoes on the pizza were cold (strange to me) and they didn't have a server. I think I was just taken aback as I expected a full service spot.
Great fresh PIZZA

The margarita pizza was the best pizza I have had, perhaps ever. They used a wood burning stove, all their ingrediants had no added chemicals or preservatives, and it was a really cute little store, with seating. Excellent service, with cute little pizzas. I would definitely recommend.
you have to try it! this is called the real Italian food.

Great crust topped with a slightly sweet  sauce, fresh mozzarella, and basil sprigs, drizzled with a touch of olive oil. A perfect balance of flavors that melt in your mouth. What I’m saying is this was the best Margherita pie I’ve had in a long time. Fresh ingredients, friendly owner, clean, inviting atmosphere. The pie came out of the fire oven in about 90 seconds and was gone about two minutes later. Leaving made me a little sad.
Best pizza in the neighborhood by far.  We love this place.  Crust is perfect, pizza delivers flavor through tomato sauce and pesto rather than cheese.
Great service. Hot food made fresh. Can't beat it.
Tried a few times. Orders were incorrect or not as described on menu. Their pesto is just basil. Not good value.
Every single item I have tried is amazing service is even better  5 stars all the way eggplant is amazing the pizza amazing just tried the wings oh my goodness !!  U.  Need to try it
Visited on early on a Sunday evening. The server seems very unenthusiastic. The food was decent but the food seems very over priced at $20+ for a 14" pie.
